display="inline"><![CDATA[L\in \mathcal {L}(V)]]></fr:tex> be a linear operator on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. We call a subspace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U\subseteq  V]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Invariant</html:dfn> under <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> if for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  U]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L(u)\in  U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>That is to say, the image of every vector in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> under <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> remains in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>. So <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L(U)\subseteq  U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
